Analysis: What has been done: We followed the prescribed workflow across metrics, traces, and logs. Global thresholds (p95/p5) were computed per component-KPI using full series; metric anomalies were detected inside the incident window (2021-03-09 21:00–21:30 UTC+8); KPI-level faults were aggregated and filtered for consecutive/severe breaches; traces were analyzed and target extraction performed to map anomalous inter-service calls to candidate components; logs and error_logs were searched within the incident window.

What the data shows: 
- A sudden, system-wide onset at 2021-03-09 21:00:00+08:00 where many components exhibit anomalies (DBs, caches, app nodes, IG/MG, apache). 
- The single largest KPI deviation is MG02 OSLinux-OSLinux_NETWORK_NETWORK_TCP-FIN-WAIT with breach_ratio ~9.0 (very large relative spike). 
- MG01 and MG02 are the top anomalous trace targets (highest trace-anomaly counts), receiving heavy incoming row_count and duration_p95 spikes from many sources (dockerB2/dockerA*/Tomcat/IG). dockerB2 is the dominant upstream source in those traces. 
